reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars So far I LOVE this light for my puzzle table
reviews.reviewText: I just purchased and received this light about 1 week ago. Attached it to my large puzzle table (approximately 4'x3') and it helps so much. It seems nice and sturdy and love the total arm length as the stiff upright part together with the flexible part allow me to have the light up out of my way and well over the board without getting in my way. Also love that it's very unobtrusive and neat and that it clamps easily onto my table (which is 3/4" plywood) without having to be taking up a lot of table top space that so many lamp/light bases take up. (Plus, as I made my table by attaching it to a drafting table type of frame so that I can have slant the table when I wish, table top lamps/lights tend to slide/fall off the table when it is slanted... not good.) The flexible part of this light's arm is the best I've had on anything and so easy to adjust just how I want it at any given time. I love that the light bar is attached to the flex arm on a ball joint, thereby making it so easy to move it around to get the light focused just where I need it in order to avoid any glare off the puzzle pieces. Plus, being able to adjust the light color itself is also great for as the light changes in the room from bright sunny days, to overcast days and long nights. (Yes, I get hooked on my puzzles and spend many a time working on them well into the wee morning hours.) Note that it just comes with the usb cord but no AC Adapter, but as I, like many of us, have several USB plug adapters left over from old phones, tablets, Kindle's, etc., it really was not a problem at all for me. Just wanted to note that to make you aware of it. Again, highly recommend this light!Now to give it the test of time to see how well it lasts, but I'm not too concerned there as it does appear to be a good solid light and fits the purpose I was wanting it for perfectly.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Decent, but lacks remote compatibility (always starts "off" if the power is cut)
reviews.reviewText: It has good light output, and I like how I can control the color temperature from white to orange/evening. My only criticism is, it can only be turned on by supplying power to it, then walking up to it, finding the button on the cord, and pressing the power button. It is unable to be controlled remotely with a smart plug, because if this lamp loses power, when it regains power it will always be in the "off" state. So, I can only use this lamp when the lights are already on in the room so I can find the switch for this lamp, and I'm already sitting at the desk, only using this lamp to amplify the lighting in the room already present. Also, it's bendy. Nice!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Get it if you have small space for a lamp on your desk
reviews.reviewText: So glad I made this purchase. I didn’t have a lot of room on my height adjustable desk for my old lamp and came across this one. It was super easy to assemble and install on my desk. The cord is also long enough to adjust to the different heights as I move my desk up and down. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 14, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This light is exactly what I was looking for. It's so simple to put together a child can do it. I was able to clamp it to a 3 inch piece of wood that I have on my desk which made it convenient for me since I did not want to clamp it onto the plexiglass. It gave me enough height that I did not have to worry about it truly being in the way. It also ended up being a great light for my camera. The clamps for the light itself are a little flimsy but once you get them in place they stay nicely. It does not come with a plug for the light itself however I plugged it into my hard drive this way I did not have to worry about any additional plugs. Great product!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 21, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good light but switch should be located differently
reviews.reviewText: I use this light on my puzzle table. Overall it is a good light. It clamps down easily, good light, multiple light output settings, easily adjustable, and the switch works good. My only complaint is that the switch is located in the cord and it is halfway between the lamp and the plug. That means to change settings or to turn it on or off I have to get up and walk around the table to reach the switch. Not a big deal, I know, but it would be nice if the switch was located right at the lamp instead of 3 or 4 feet away.

Lots of lighting options from temperature of the light colour to colour brightness. The flexible arm looks great as it appears to look like the metal arm and stays put. The light bar itself is on a ball bearing swivel so you could angle many ways including facing the light upwards instead of downwards of you choose. Great product. USB connection only but works well when in a USB plug as well.

reviews.reviewerName: Leonardo Del Bosque EspinosaLeonardo Del Bosque Espinosa
reviews.reviewText: Diseño discreto. La variación en la intensidad y en los modos de iluminación permite crear un espacio de trabajo agradable. Los materiales de fabricación se perciben duraderos.
Excelente calidad, la intensidad es muy buena y se puede regular y tambien el color se regula entre blanco y calido.

It has warm and cool lights settings and it’s dimmable! Which makes it fantastic for reading, drawing, painting nails, whatever.Also, I didn’t realize this was a usb plug instead of a wall plug. Awesome. We had a power outage immediately after I got it after a tornado and I realized that I could just plug it into my solar powdered power bank and have a nice reading light even during power outages, camping, etc. The power goes out a lot here. It’s better than I could have imagined and the design is sleek and simple and non bulky. I love that it’s adjustable. Perfect not taking up space on my desk and go anywhere lamp.

reviews.reviewTitle: Works fine and feels sturdy, but lit could be a bit brighter
reviews.reviewText: The product fits great at the edge of my table and stands firmly. It's easy to bend it around to adjust the focus of the light. Great value for the price. However, the light is not as bright as other table lamps I have used before. It's fine for casual lighting when using computer, but may not be sufficient for non-computer bench work.
